{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 159060, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "50019", "body": "His weapon is not a sword, its a staff, download Model Viewer and look at the item/weapon tab for \"Stave_blacktemple\". It should be the 3rd or so of about 5 or so. It is a awesome model, great detail and craftmanship went into, too bad its not a in-game item. It would the staff to end all staffs lol.", "date": "2007-09-26T22:47:20-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Wrong, the Death Knights of the Scourge wield Runeblades, and they're a completely different order. Gorefiend and all the other horde Death Knights of the Second War used staves.", "creationdate": "2007-10-16T21:34:04-05:00", "id": 313993, "rating": 9, "commentid": 159060, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "83142", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Except that Teron is not a Scourge Death Knight. Teron, instead, is an Orcish Death Knight -- the First of many created by the Warlock Gul'dan on the orders of then-Warchief Doomhammer.", "creationdate": "2008-01-27T03:06:24-06:00", "id": 24190, "rating": 32, "commentid": 159060, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "eclipsegsx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This nub is an orc? Always thought he was a human by the way he walks/moves. Strange", "creationdate": "2008-04-16T08:05:47-05:00", "id": 332376, "rating": 1, "commentid": 159060, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Twan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Teron Gorefiend, like all of the Orcish death knights, has the spirit of an orcish necrolyte and the body of a human knight slain in the First War.   Or so my Warcraft 2 manual says.", "creationdate": "2008-04-16T14:20:26-05:00", "id": 31221, "rating": 51, "commentid": 159060, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Asmodoues", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "correct! he is an orc warlock spirit in a dead human's body; 1st generation death knight", "creationdate": "2010-03-11T23:53:04-06:00", "id": 153601, "rating": 7, "commentid": 159060, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "517216", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 193724, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "25227", "body": "A little reminder that is actually missing from most strategies, the pet bar will look like this:\r\n\r\n1 Spirit Strike (melee attack, use on Teron if you are done with Constructs)\r\n2 empty\r\n3 Spirit Lance (slowing attack)\r\n4 Spirit Chains (AoE shackle)\r\n5 Spirit Volley (AoE attack)\r\n6 empty\r\n7 Spirit Shield\r\n\r\nWith this you can bind easy to access keys to those from game options as having quick access to 3, 4 and 5 is very important. Killing Constructs is fun!", "date": "2007-11-30T02:52:45-06:00", "rating": 62, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Awesome! That's exactly what I was looking to find.  Are these abilities linked to a global cooldown?", "creationdate": "2008-01-25T08:45:08-06:00", "id": 323472, "rating": 4, "commentid": 193724, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "27334", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 196251, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Remedy", "body": "Today we confirmed that hearthing while affected with Shadow of Death will spawn your constructs as soon as you leave the instance.", "date": "2007-12-05T04:05:50-06:00", "rating": 50, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 200974, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "quzzap", "body": "http://www.ferox-horde.de/feroxtgs2/\n\nThis is a simulator in which you can practice the part when you get the shadow of death debuff in the Teron Gorefiend fight, after 55 seconds you die and become a ghost which you can control. 4 constructs spawn and try to get to your raid & will slow+damage the raid you must stop that from happening.\n\nBest is to aoe first (Spirit Volley) (has 15 sec CD) then aoe shackle (Spirit Chains) right after it, then tab target all 4 constructs and Spirit Lance each of them. The slowing from Spirit Lance stays on for 9secs and can be stacked up to 3 times (which causes 90% movement reduction and they'll barely move) so make sure you're Spirit Lancing each construct fast. When everything goes fine they should be dead after 2 shackles (and are on half way to the raid).\n\nWhen you're done killing your pack (the simulator stops here) you should help out others with the debuff and nuke their constructs.\n\nGL ! =]\n\nedit: fixed link", "date": "2007-12-14T03:38:13-06:00", "rating": 46, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Note of clarification: after the first Chains, you should apply a single movement debuff to each of the four and then rotate through them again in the same order.  This makes them move so slow you could just continue the rotation until they're all dead.  A second round of aoe is a bonus but be careful not to let one get away from you if its debuff wears off.  Starting with the mobs closer to the raid means they'll get the 2nd stack of debuff first on your next rotation, causing the ones behind to catch up and aid aoe control.", "creationdate": "2008-01-18T16:24:52-06:00", "id": 23475, "rating": 8, "commentid": 200974, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sounder", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Fair warning, this is much harder than the ACTUAL event. So if you can't get it down, it's more because of the flash version, but you should at least know what you're doing.", "creationdate": "2008-07-03T08:29:27-05:00", "id": 38287, "rating": 3, "commentid": 200974, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "TheMuffinMan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Links broken...took me to some shopping webpage....", "creationdate": "2012-08-24T10:01:07-05:00", "id": 566034, "rating": -1, "commentid": 200974, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Scourgepretzels", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-07-08T13:07:36-05:00", 2, "quzzap"]}
