{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 213272, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ambusher", "body": "A little lore just for fun:\n\nTeron gorefiend was once one of Gul'dan's warlocks, before Doomhammer destroyed most of Gul'dan's Shadow Council, which consisted of warlocks (and probably also some other of Gul'dan's servants). Before becoming leader of the Horde, Doomhammer also destroyed the former Horde leader, Blackhand, who was under the control of Gul'dan. Doomhammer was also about to finish Gul'dan, who had been \"sleeping\" during this whole slaughter, but he spared Gul'dan, who convinced Doomhammer that he would need his powers if he were to conquer Azeroth. Gul'dan promised to help the Horde by making some kind of army to add to the Horde, and he did. Teron Gorefiend, who was a former warlock and slain by Doomhammer, was raised again by Gul'dan and his ogre companion Cho'gall and had his soul put into a human corpse (who had been slain during the Horde's siege of Stormwind) with new and enhanced powers. Teron Gorefiend is a so-called Death Knight.\n\nHow he ended up in Black Temple, however, I don't know.", "date": "2008-01-05T11:28:18-06:00", "rating": 59, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just to expand on the above post, it is important that you stay up front with the raid until about 20 seconds before the debuff expires.  The reasons for this are twofold:  1.  It gives your raid that vital extra dps or healing that would otherwise be wasted, as this is a dps-intensive encounter. 2.  Doom Blossoms will still hit you from across the room.  If you are not a healer, this means that you could die early and spawn the constructs early.  It is important that you do not do that, as dying early may not give the ghost before you ample time to help you with your constructs (because they'", "creationdate": "2008-01-05T11:28:19-06:00", "id": 333771, "rating": 11, "commentid": 213272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "133472", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "From the little strat guide above:  \"Once you die from the mark of death, you are spawned at the back of the room along with Shadowy Constructs.\"  Just to clarify, when the Shadow of Death timer runs out, you will die and spawn the ghosts [b]where you are currently standing.[/b] It doesn't teleport you to the back of the room, you need to run there yourself.  edit: didn't mean to reply to the above post but what the hey.", "creationdate": "2008-01-14T00:56:07-06:00", "id": 23139, "rating": 45, "commentid": 213272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "65908", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He ended up in the Black Temple when the Alliance attacked it. Turalyon dueled Gorefiend and killed his body. His Soul however, escaped into the skies. perhaps he found a new body after the Cataclysm of Draenor.", "creationdate": "2009-12-10T17:54:44-06:00", "id": 136468, "rating": 6, "commentid": 213272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Monday", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Though this is fairly dated post, I thought I'd add that you as a player actually help him to find a body by completing a few quests in Shadowmoon Valley (starting with http://www.wowhead.com/quest=10642 if you're Alliance, http://www.wowhead.com/quest=10624 if you're Horde). He possesses you and forces you to kill the person keeping him captive before escaping, presumably to the Black Temple.", "creationdate": "2012-01-16T02:32:04-06:00", "id": 508631, "rating": 8, "commentid": 213272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Seosaimhin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Also it should be noted he pledged his loyalty to Doomhammer and the Horde, and after the Horde was defeated by the Alliance in the Second War, he did keep his promise and helped reform the Horde to lead them to other worlds, giving up his (SECOND) life to buy Ner'zhul more time to open his portals. Teron Gorefiend was (at least before WOD changed it) never loyal to Gul'dan, he was loyal to the Horde, which at the time was technically lead by Gul'dan, thus he was \"loyal\" to him. The gorefiend we knew nvr woulda left the horde alongside gul'dan as it is in WOD", "creationdate": "2015-02-21T00:56:25-06:00", "id": 841801, "rating": 0, "commentid": 213272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "conmanW", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-01-05T11:29:46-06:00", 2, "Ambusher"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 229181, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "82795", "body": "Noob question, but is there anything to decipher which constructs are yours versus your neighbors? or is it just that the timer is spaced that there can't really be more than one set of constructs in the same part of the field. (Unless of course they aren't tagged and bolting for the raid. O_O)", "date": "2008-02-04T02:06:50-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No way to decipher that, besides you can target other peoples ghosts so it doesn't make much difference. There won't be 2 sets of constructs up unless it takes you or the other guy over 30 secs to kill them, which shouldn't really happen.  Bit off topic here, but when running to the back of the room don't run through or near the constructs, you don't want to aggro them and die before you reach the corner.", "creationdate": "2008-02-04T04:08:15-06:00", "id": 24807, "rating": 10, "commentid": 229181, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "65908", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
