{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 275211, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "23311", "body": "One thing to note about the Ghost phase. If you're using a bar mod add-on such as Bongos, you will not have your \"main\" bar get replaced by the Ghost bar. Instead, you will have to use your pet bar. \r\n\r\nI countered this by employing 3 macros set up on a different, unused bar that I make visible only during the Teron encounter. The macros read as:\r\n\r\n/cast Spirit Chains\r\n/cast Spirit Lance\r\n/cast Spirit Volley\r\n\r\nYou may also choose to macro Spirit Shield and Strike, however as they are not the most priority spells I feel just as safe click-casting them once my Constructs are dead. Macroing the critical spells and hot-keying them goes a long way towards cutting down your Constructs once you get hit with SoD.\r\n\r\nOne other suggestion-- start spamming Spirit Chains seconds before you die. You want to make sure that it gets cast IMMEDIATELY when you die and your Constructs spawn. Speed is everything here, the faster the Constructs get the inital lock-down the faster you can start tabbing through them to Lance them. Some people recommend doing a Volley THEN a chains, and this is fine if you're practiced enough with the Ghosts, but if not, opening with Chains is far safer. You will have ample time to drop your ghosts before they get to the raid even if you do not open with Volley.\r\n\r\nAfter that it's just a matter of practice. The game linked in this thread is good, but it is nowhere near as good as practical experience. \r\n\r\nThis fight is considered the best test of a raid's DPS, as the fight allows your DPS to do nothing but attack the boss unless they get hit with Shadow of Death. Because of the nature of Gorefiend's abilities, the higher your raid's DPS the better. Recommend opening with MDs onto the tank and Bloodlusts all around when able to make sure that both initial threat is high and that damage on Teron is high from the opening, so long as no one is generating more threat than your tank, of course.", "date": "2008-04-21T09:28:30-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Bartender3 will automatically replace your first bar with your ghost's abilities.", "creationdate": "2008-04-30T17:44:35-05:00", "id": 333770, "rating": 0, "commentid": 275211, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "133472", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 282247, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "139868", "body": "to me it seems that on the screenshot of him he is human..but in the 3D he is orc..wtf?", "date": "2008-05-04T13:15:08-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As someone already said, Teron was a Orc warlock but Doomhammer killed him, when Gul'dan created a order of Death knigths for the Horde, he ressurected Teron and others by putting their spirit into human knights that were killed in the first war. So that is why he looks human.", "creationdate": "2008-05-06T06:06:39-05:00", "id": 32864, "rating": 11, "commentid": 282247, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "52272", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What he ment to say is, the 3D model viewer still shows Teron wearing something similar to the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/itemset=646]Corrupter Raiment (warlock T5)[/url] which was his model used before patch 2.4.0 when they made a new model for him in Black Temple.  Wowhead still hasn't updated the 3D model viewer, and it also looks like Teron's truncheon isn't updated for the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/search?q=Teron+Gorefiend,+I+am...]Teron Gorfiend, I am quest...[/url] .  He is still using [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=13937]Headmaster's Charge[/url].", "creationdate": "2010-08-25T15:16:52-05:00", "id": 179147, "rating": 2, "commentid": 282247, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "strongarm91", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The 3D model viewer at the top of the page does indeed show the incorrect model, even at the time of this writing.", "creationdate": "2012-02-21T09:44:05-06:00", "id": 521382, "rating": 0, "commentid": 282247, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Donegan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 285100, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "150500", "body": "This is a relativley simple battle as long as the entire raid knows whats they are doing. When he casts shadow of death, you are still able to do some damage before you die. When the time is almost up, run to one of the corners. When you spawn back as a ghost, immediatley use the ice blast skill to freeze all of them. Then, just use the skill set on numbe 2 switching between mobs to kill them. It is seriously reccommended that you practice using\r\n\r\nhttp://www.ferox-horde.de/feroxtgs2/\r\n\r\nBe aware that you will still probably screw up your first time no matter how many times you play the game. As long as the first person to get the debuff gets his/hers down quickly. Everyone can start helping everyone else get down their mobs. Try to use soulstones or ressurections as much as possible to get people up when they die. A bad combonation of who he debuffs can easily cause a failiure. Have fun!", "date": "2008-05-09T10:47:26-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 288365, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "152034", "body": "Lore-wise Teron Gorefiend's story can be found here http://www.wowwiki.com/Teron_gorefiend\r\n \r\nHere's the brief cap\r\nHe was a orc warlock of the shadow council, died by the hands of Doomhammer's followers, but Gul'dans assistants reanimated him into the first Death Knight. As a powerful Death Knight, he was asigned by Ner'Zhul to capture the Eye of Dalaran from the mage-city of Dalaran, his attempt failed and he fled to Shadowmoon Valley, where he committed suicide after slaying his Death Knight followers. \r\n\r\nHe looks more human-like than orcish because Gul'Dan used a human knight's body to be reanimated into Teron Gorefiend", "date": "2008-05-14T21:02:09-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Where did you read that suicide part? First of all, he managed to get the Eye of Dalaran with the assistance of Deathwing. Later, he was killed by Turalyon at the Black Temple, while he was defending Ner'zhul, to complete his spell to open portals to another worlds.", "creationdate": "2013-05-27T09:43:19-05:00", "id": 663009, "rating": 0, "commentid": 288365, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Xafire", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 295099, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "79144", "body": "A rogue in my raid found out that he could avoid Shadow of Death by vanishing as it was cast if he was the target. Could anyone else confirm this? It may also be possible to cancel his cast with feign death or bubble.", "date": "2008-05-26T16:26:39-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tactics like that work for several boss spells.  Illhoof's Sacrifice spell is another example of something you can avoid if you're quick enough to Vanish/Feign Death before the cast completes.", "creationdate": "2008-05-29T20:47:35-05:00", "id": 34985, "rating": 4, "commentid": 295099, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Senka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 316204, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Osmigos", "body": "A small trick to increase damage on this fight:\nTank him facing the way you came in with all the melee behind him and all the range/healers in front on the stair side. This will cause him to turn and face the melee less often while casting on random raid members, reducing the number of parries, and increasing melee dps.\n\nAlso: Snake traps are *very* useful, as the snakes can be chosen as targets for his random shadow bolts instead of a raid member.", "date": "2008-06-29T14:01:27-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You do realise that what he meant was that on the pull, the ranged dps should be dpsing from behind the main tank. Because Gorefiend has to face the target to cast Shadow of Death, in this set-up, there will be a lower chance for Gorefiend to turn around and parry the melee group while he's casting Shadow of Death, because most of the possible targets are already in front of him.  If the entire raid was behind Gorefiend, with only the main tank in front, every time Gorefiend casts Shadow of Death, he will certainly turn around to face the raid (where the target is )and parry quite a few attack", "creationdate": "2008-06-29T14:01:28-05:00", "id": 341222, "rating": 5, "commentid": 316204, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "88503", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What you posted makes little sense.   I may be just misunderstanding what you're trying to say. Melee DPS should NEVER be attacking the front of a boss or else not only are they nerfing their own DPS but they're also greatly increasing the boss's damage because they'll get parried quite a bit.  Additionally, no unit, PC or NPC, can dodge or parry while casting.  Anyway, I do agree that snake traps are the way to go here.", "creationdate": "2008-06-30T11:26:38-05:00", "id": 339941, "rating": 2, "commentid": 316204, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Senka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You did misunderstand. I ment that Teron is facing the stairs, where all the ranged are, and there are no ranged behind him, so he won't turn toward the melee to cast at anyone except the melee themselves. I edited it and fixed the wording to make it clearer.", "creationdate": "2008-06-30T17:52:20-05:00", "id": 339977, "rating": 0, "commentid": 316204, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Osmigos", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Sorry, I did misunderstand.  He can't parry or dodge while casting Shadow of Death because that has a cast time, but he does turn to target people with Incinerate.  His Incinerate is instant, so he can parry and dodge during that time.  I forgot about that.", "creationdate": "2008-07-15T17:43:18-05:00", "id": 39704, "rating": 1, "commentid": 316204, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Senka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-06-30T17:54:34-05:00", 1, "Osmigos"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 318773, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rasztra", "body": "First off, a little shadow resist helps so if you have any of the Ashtongue craftable SR items, throw one or two of them on.\r\n\r\nHere's what you do when you get Shadow of Death:\r\n\r\n1.  When the debuff is at ~20 seconds, move to the spot (back corner of the room).\r\n2.  [U]Face the corner[/U] and put your [U]back to the boss[/U].\r\n3.  As soon as you see them pop up, do the AoE called [U]Spirit Volley[/U] (hotkey 5). You should still be facing the corner with your back to the boss.\r\n4.  Immediately after the AoE, do the Frost Nova AoE called [U]Spirit Chains[/U] (hotkey 4).\r\n5.  Back up a little bit so that you are between the constructs and Teron Gorefiend.  Your back should STILL be facing Gorefiend.\r\n6.  Now, you first need to [U]Spirit Lance them at least once each[/U] in a cycle.  [I]This can be done by tab targeting (which should target the closest one first, if you are positioned correctly) or by clicking.  I have done both and they both work.  I find the best is to click them each one-by-one and press \"3\".[/I]\r\n7.  After they are all hit once and slowed, just start Spirit Lancing whichever one is closest to you.  If another construct passes it and gets closer, switch to that one.\r\n8.  If you are Pro, when the AoE cooldown is up, use it again followed immediately by a Frost Nova (the AoE takes the slowing effects off).\r\n9.  If you do this correctly, your constructs will be dead before they even reach halfway to the raid.  /flex and brag in raid chat, then use your remaining time to go help the next person with their constructs.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI know that seems like a lot to take in, but it really isn't.  Here is a summary:\r\n\r\nWhen you die from the debuff, move to the spot and put your [u]back[/u] to Gorefiend.  [b]Stay between the constructs and the raid the whole time.[/b]  Do Spirit Volley (AoE) -> Spirit Chains (Frost Nova) -> Spirit Lance in that order (5, 4, 3, switch target, 3, switch target, 3...).", "date": "2008-07-03T08:54:19-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 334539, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "162450", "body": "/script SetCVar(\"targetNearestDistance\", 20)\r\n/targetenemy\r\n/cast Spirit Lance\r\n/script SetCVar(\"targetNearestDistance\", 41) \r\n\r\nIs a great macro for this fight, set with a binding close to the tab button, spamming this and tab while standing in front of the constructs works wonders. With this macro you can spam it and kill your constructs and if done well, you can still have enough time to help others.", "date": "2008-07-24T03:22:43-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 343932, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "166807", "body": "Just so you know it. When doing him yesterday, we wiped and I got DI from a pally.\r\nWhile waiting for the rest to die, he cast Shadow of Death on me although I was bubbled.\r\nFortunately I also had SS on me.", "date": "2008-08-03T23:52:38-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 346917, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Caudric", "body": "Is his health listed correctly? From what I've seen he has 5.8 million health not the 5 he has in the Quick Facts box.", "date": "2008-08-07T13:15:40-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Actually he got 3.6mln right now, You could nuke him down easily befeore any constrcuts approach the raid group.", "creationdate": "2008-11-07T17:53:15-06:00", "id": 359209, "rating": 0, "commentid": 346917, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "47651", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 366163, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vlad", "body": "[code]#showtooltip\n/castsequence reset=4 Spirit Volley,Spirit Chains,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance,Spirit Lance[/code]\n\nYou can use that macro for all the spells you need to use to kill the constructs.\n[ol]\n[li]AoE volley (damage)[/li]\n[li]Frost Nova (freeze)[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 2 times on Construct #1[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 2 times on Construct #2[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 2 times on Construct #3[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 2 times on Construct #4[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 1 time on Construct #1[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 1 time on Construct #2[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 1 time on Construct #3[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance 1 time on Construct #4[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance what ever Construct you feel should be slowed some more[/li]\n[li]Ice Lance what ever Construct you feel should be slowed some more[/li]\n[/ol]\nMacro will repeat with AoE then Frost Nova, e.g.", "date": "2008-08-31T14:27:47-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "since spirit lance is an instant cast, has no CD and no global CD (according to the wowhead spirit lance info) could I just make a macro to cast 5 at once like: /cast spirit lance /cast spirit lance /cast spirit lance /cast spirit lance /cast spirit lance  This would mow down the constructs quickly but it seems too easy.  I'd like to hear what other people think before testing it in the raid.", "creationdate": "2008-09-03T12:54:16-05:00", "id": 348494, "rating": 0, "commentid": 366163, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "30863", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There is a 1 second global cooldown triggered by the spirit lance, a macro like that will not work.", "creationdate": "2008-09-04T13:25:11-05:00", "id": 45598, "rating": 0, "commentid": 366163, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kuipo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "you have volley twice.   your second action should be Spirit Chains", "creationdate": "2008-09-09T07:52:53-05:00", "id": 46082, "rating": 0, "commentid": 366163, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Augos", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You are right and I fixed my typo. The macro should work too, you just need to use it according to what it casts, so you don't waste too many Ice Lances on the \"wrong\" mob and letting the others run to the raid. :)", "creationdate": "2008-09-18T04:14:07-05:00", "id": 47059, "rating": 4, "commentid": 366163, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Vlad", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-09-18T04:13:25-05:00", 1, "Vlad"]}
