{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 590757, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "258919", "body": "This boss has been nerfed like hell. With a decent 73+ raid of about 18 or so, you can burn down this boss before the ghost mobs reach your group more than once.\r\n\r\nTurn on shadow protection to be safe and pay attention to your debuffs, but to be honest, this guy is no longer very hard in comparison to other bosses in the Temple, and with enough DPS he'll hit it in a minute or so.", "date": "2009-02-01T10:04:20-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 623015, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "1337Thanatos", "body": "lore-wise blizz screwed up with this guy. For one thing, the first death knights were orcs in human bodies, meaning if he was just another old death knight he should have a human skin, but Teron is special, as in the quest chain you do about him he posseses a draenei body, so he should have a draenei skin, but instead, he still has an orc skin\n\nEDIT : also, he's a death knight, so he should still be serving Arthas (seeing as how he wasn't in the scarlet enclave with the rest of us, he should still be enslaved) and Arthas was almost killed by Illidan, which in my book, makes them mortal enemies! so how is he serving Illidan? a mistake IMO on blizz's part", "date": "2009-02-25T12:53:22-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Teron Gorefiend is THE original Death Knight, and specifically an Orc that was 'trapped' in a human body.  You got that part right.  But he didn't possess that Draenei's body...he killed his spirit's jailor so that he could be completely free to do as he pleased.  Specifically, he has the same odd human visage he had at the end of WC2...or at least an artistic representation of it.  As far as him being a Death Knight and Arthas being involved:  1) He's in another dimension, how exactly would Arthas manage to control him?  Arthas is powerful now, but not THAT powerful.  2) He's not related to t", "creationdate": "2009-02-25T12:53:23-06:00", "id": 392854, "rating": 5, "commentid": 623015, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Flenop", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "/clap everything right except outland isnt another dimension its another planet......or it was.", "creationdate": "2009-05-16T15:15:10-05:00", "id": 98349, "rating": 1, "commentid": 623015, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Treld", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=21877]Karsius the Ancient Watcher[/url]  That is the draenei 1337Thanatos is talking about, and that draenei is the jailor of Teron's spirit/soul. Which is aswell the reason why Teron possesses your body, to defeat Karsius so he would be able to do as he wish, as Flenop said.", "creationdate": "2011-03-19T08:45:40-05:00", "id": 233129, "rating": 0, "commentid": 623015, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "615407", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-02-25T13:01:22-06:00", 1, "1337Thanatos"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 745974, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "rauxon", "body": "Just tried this with a group of bored 80s.  most of us are in heroic 5 man (blue/purple/emblem) gear.  7 people (tankadin, healadin, shadow priest, shaman, warrior, and rogue) got to him with only trash wipes - primarily down to the fact that we'd never been there before and we weren't careful enough about patrols.\r\n\r\nHowever - at Teron, it all went to pieces.  We just couldn't do enough damage to get him down before we lost too many members of the group to be \"viable\".  Got him down to about 1.2 million on first attempt, and 900k on second - and stopped since it's getting a bit late. ;)\r\n\r\nI think that with 8 (just 1 more DPS) it wouldn't have been that much of a problem.  The issue of taking out the constructs is probably still the only real challenge, other than that it wasn't too bad.\r\n\r\nHope this helps anyone trying to decide what to do on a bored evening ;)", "date": "2009-06-13T19:20:20-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You need roughly 41,200 DPS to kill him before anyone dies from Shadow of Death (30 second cast, 55 seconds to take effect). Your group would have, at absolute maximum, four minutes and twenty-five seconds (just under five minutes with an additional person) to win, disregarding the implications of losing a healer or tank, or getting hit with Constructs, as smaller groups are more vulnerable to Shadow of Death.", "creationdate": "2010-11-21T12:58:30-06:00", "id": 193571, "rating": -1, "commentid": 745974, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "689829", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
