{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 1499346, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "WorgN6", "body": "Just did it as prot in 360 ret gear.\n\n7.8k DPS (7m40s~)\n470k Taken\n455k Healed\n\n20s WOG, Holy Radiance were enough to keep me safe the whole time, but I like to play it careful and save HP/LOH/AD/GOAK. \n\nUsed Seal of Truth, Blessing of Might, STR Flask from alchemey's \"Flask of Enhancement\" and Grounded Plasma Shield from engineering twice. (36k~ total absorbed from it.)\n\nHe doesn't do much damage, you'll resist the shadowbolt nonsense and the other nasty mechanics don't apply to the \"tank.\"\n\nI wouldn't be surprised if he's perfectly easy as ret with Last Word and Selfless Healer, but I'm used to using prot like this so...", "date": "2011-08-20T11:44:32-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-08-20T11:46:26-05:00", 1, "WorgN6"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 1500903, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sorsa", "body": "Fury warrior in troll/justice gear, extremely nasty to solo, first attempt I did with dual mending 2 handers (vastly more Mending procs per minute over 1handers, tested out on dummies, with dual 2h mending you get almost 50% more mending hps), that ended with a ~10% wipe, 40s before second enraged regen was ready.\r\n\r\nSecond attempt in prot gear and some dps pieces to reach 8% hit and 26 expertise, then stayed in def stance and kept debuffs up and stance danced to use colossus smash for extra dps, long story short barely killed him within 9minutes and 50s, 10s short from enrage. Also had 90 strength food buff, and flask of titanic strength, as well as blessing of might from pally alt parked outside for the fight.", "date": "2011-08-22T11:17:00-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 1503015, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Pengalor", "body": "My friend and I (hunter and rogue) duo BT every week and this fight was one of the more challenging to get a strategy for. We tried burning him down, not enough dps and one person handling the ghosts didn't work. Tried having me solo it, didn't work (apparently my pet counts as another person so he still casts the debuff). However, what we did figure out is he won't cast the debuff if he is fighting my friend and I stay in Feign Death. So now our strategy is I stay in FD and he soloes it as long as he can manage. When he can't handle the damage anymore I get my pet out and get it some threat and then we both burn CDs. It works surprisingly well and we clear it in one shot every week : ).", "date": "2011-08-25T07:53:01-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
