{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 1632193, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MABGamer6407", "body": "Man He needs to drop that Staff, Pole-arm What ever it is. Im kinda shockd as often Certain Boss's  (Usely a big type of 1 like end boss's or 1s with history) drop There weapon For Gameplay prepossess. Like Strormrage Can Drop his Weapons so what Not Him? Any how even as 85 this guy is a tricky fight We had some truble with hm on my Mage As 1 member has to Control the fight as a Ghost an He does Quite a Bit Of fearing, Took some time but we Did get him down. I think there was me an 2-3 others.", "date": "2012-02-26T19:51:50-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-02-26T19:52:51-06:00", 1, "MABGamer6407"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 1641034, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TdarKoNe", "body": "We duo this as an item level 371 Blood Death Knight, 390 Elemental Shaman.\r\n\r\nWith 2 level 85's this fight is pretty simple as long as you have the DPS for it. He will cast \"Shadow of Death\" on any play EXCEPT whoever is tanking him, which kills them after 55 seconds and turn them into a ghost. When this happens it will spawn several \"shadow constructs\" that can only be killed by a ghost player. Other than that his damage isn't too bad and you're only real concern will be beating his enrage timer.\r\n\r\nFull video of the fight : http://youtu.be/OnVcCJ9xfkQ", "date": "2012-03-18T10:48:46-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
