{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 1784181, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dust", "body": "Teron Gorefiend is similar to an earlier boss in the instance, [npc=22887], in that if you have a pet or minion out, you'll make things very difficult on yourself and possibly (likely) wipe.  Ditch your pet or minion and enjoy an easy solo.", "date": "2012-12-19T14:52:48-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-19T14:55:33-06:00", 2, "Dust"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 64, "id": 1814832, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sway79", "body": "I dont know if they have changed this fight at all recently, but i just killed him with a 90 bm hunter. I started with my pet out and burned all cds, once they had all be useup i dimissed my pet and than kited him around for a bit. once he hit 20% i resummoned my pet and burned him down the rest of the way", "date": "2013-02-17T15:22:45-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can also just Feign Death and wait for your pet to kill him ;)", "creationdate": "2013-02-26T09:46:54-06:00", "id": 635852, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1814832, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Naglfarr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 1823869, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "benx2011", "body": "dont need to dismiss your pet. same as fighting High Warlord Naj'entusas, as long as you turn off your pet taunt and you have the aggro. you wont get wiped.", "date": "2013-03-07T15:33:37-06:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Works great! Soloed w/ this method as i479 BM Hunter. Burn your CD's at the beginning to pull threat and the rest is easy. I used spirit mend once at 83%hp just for chits and giggles. Happy Hunting (+)", "creationdate": "2013-04-21T07:01:55-05:00", "id": 652685, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1823869, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pod32", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks. I am hunter Lvl90 and I did Soloed and it worked. :)", "creationdate": "2013-11-11T20:21:42-06:00", "id": 707434, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1823869, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "midobu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you are soloing and you are a hunter, you need to avoid his \"Shadow of Death\". Try using some of those tactics here to see if it will work for you. Try not to use a tanking pet (like a turtle) instead you need to be a tank. Also \"Spirit Bond (Both you and pet regenerate 3% of total health every 2 sec)\" talent will help you and your pet both alive without having major healing to you and your pet. Turned off \"Growl\" from your pet. Put your pet \"Passive\" mode for the entire fight and use \"Kill command\" to attack him then put your pet aside by using \"Move to\" command to avoid getting his aggro.", "creationdate": "2014-06-18T03:05:33-05:00", "id": 751976, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1823869, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "midobu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 1838591, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "1110532", "body": "Note to mages that are soloing him. dont cast mirror images, it will cause you to most likely get the \"Shadow of Death\"", "date": "2013-04-03T15:18:34-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks for the advice. After dying a couple of times, this helped.", "creationdate": "2013-08-04T21:09:12-05:00", "id": 682724, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1838591, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jstrahan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
