{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 1946719, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Heimdallen", "body": "People have been talking about how, when solo fighting him and you have a second, targetable, combat pet or minion or whatever out, to make sure you keep aggro or else he will cast \"Shadow of Death\" on you, starting a 55 second countdown timer until you blow up and die. \r\n\r\nIn other words, if you're a hunter, from what I've read and now understand is that if your pet keeps aggro the whole time, or if you keep aggro the whole time, the buff won't be cast on you. But if threat is transferred, it is cast on you, being the only actual player in the encounter since you're soloing him. Advice from people is just simply don't have your pet out. \r\n\r\nWell, I went back to farm some Ashtongue Deathsworn rep last week and I proceeded to fight Gorefiend without any prior knowledge on how the fight worked, just assuming it was a tank n' spank with me being at level 90 with a 510 gear average. I killed him just fine and only after studying the combat log noticed that in the first few seconds of the fight, I pulled aggro from my bear and the \"Shadow of Death\" was cast on me. It wasn't an issue because he was dead about 20 seconds before the countdown hit 0. \r\n\r\nSo unless you're having problems getting him down in under 50 seconds, you'd probably never even know the debuff was cast on you. Don't worry about it if you're 90 and do decent damage.", "date": "2014-02-25T16:49:26-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
