{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 1995838, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1312041", "body": "Why are all the BC raids so horribly unfriendly to mages trying to solo them? I've had no problem doing Tempest Keep, Black Temple, and Sunwell on my Paladin and Shaman but on my mage with similar gear, everything is next to impossible to do without dying several times first. Constantly have to get rid of my pet and not use Mirror Image, which are two of the main reasons I'm normally even able to solo anything in the first place. Kind of ridiculous to keep the instant kill mechanics these days since most people solo them anyway. Why put classes that need pets etc. at such a huge disadvantage? I've never been so frustrated with this game as I have been the last couple days trying to solo Tier 4/5 and other BC raids for transmog. It's bad enough that they screwed over mages with no cool looking transmog to begin with. But to obtain the only decent set, I have to make 20 runbacks and take 10 minutes killing each boss, while on my other characters I can breeze through. Come on man.", "date": "2014-08-24T23:00:55-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
